        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3585663236" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1433546030598479691">A slow-moving plot with rich characters, this story felt exactly like real life - simple in its day-to-day actions and conversations. I can relate to the small-town attitude. When people get together after death or divorce, there is sure to be gossip, whether you like it or not, but it will eventually go away. Like my mom used to say, &quot;Flies will land on a manure pile until a fresher one comes along.&quot; Boy! I miss her witticisms!<br/><br/>This story got very personal for me. Although my dad is a recent wid</span>
  <span id="freeText1433546030598479691" style="display:none">A slow-moving plot with rich characters, this story felt exactly like real life - simple in its day-to-day actions and conversations. I can relate to the small-town attitude. When people get together after death or divorce, there is sure to be gossip, whether you like it or not, but it will eventually go away. Like my mom used to say, "Flies will land on a manure pile until a fresher one comes along." Boy! I miss her witticisms!<br /><br />This story got very personal for me. Although my dad is a recent widower, his emotions missing his wife (my mom) are still extremely raw. But as time passes, will he be interested in another woman, even if it's just for companionship? And how would I feel about it?<br /><br />Extremely moving!</span>
  <a data-text-id="1433546030598479691" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

